        "body": "Summary\n- Add PTY-based TUI integration tests covering real terminal input/render behavior against a deterministic fake TuiBackend fixture.\n- Add a local-backend PTY smoke test that runs tui --local with an isolated config and mocks only the external OpenAI-compatible model endpoint.\n- Add a focused TUI PTY GitHub Actions workflow plus a watch command for recording the actual test run.\n\nVerification\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tui/tui-pty-harness.test.ts src/tui/tui-pty-local.test.ts\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/package-scripts.test.ts\n- pnpm tui:pty:test:watch --no-alt-screen\n- git diff --check\n\nReal behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: TUI PTY tests now exercise startup, typed prompt submission, rendered responses, slash command routing, busy guards, model patching, fast-mode status, reset, and clean exit.\nReal environment tested: Local macOS worktree using node-pty pseudo-terminals; CI workflow targets Ubuntu 24.04 with Node 24.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tui/tui-pty-harness.test.ts src/tui/tui-pty-local.test.ts\nEvidence after fix: 2 test files passed, 11 tests passed.\nObserved result after fix: Fake-backend PTY coverage and local-backend PTY smoke coverage both pass; watch mode can mirror the test TUI without mixing Vitest reporter output into the alternate-screen view.\nWhat was not tested: Live provider calls, real external model APIs, full release CI, and broad cross-OS TUI behavior.\n",
